        -:  368:  * in a bug caused by aliasing.
        -:  369:  *
        -:  370:  * Notice however that this method is only useful if you want to replace a matrix by its own adjoint.
        -:  371:  * If you just need the adjoint of a matrix, use adjoint().
        -:  372:  *
        -:  373:  * \note if the matrix is not square, then \c *this must be a resizable matrix.
        -:  374:  * This excludes (non-square) fixed-size matrices, block-expressions and maps.
        -:  375:  *
